                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/940.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The groups have decided to telegraph Russia to the following effect: Japan has
                    made a proposition which is acceptable to the British, French and German
                    Governments and to all four groups, and upon approval by the American Government
                    she will be admitted, thus making five groups. Definite answer to be received
                    from Russia by June 18, else loan negotiations will proceed without her.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
